title: For Sale:  Lyman GPH Flintlock 54
postcontent: I have for sale a lightly used Lyman great plains hunter in .54 caliber.The rifle's lock time is so superb I never even installed the L&R lock that I bought for it. I am really meticulous with everything I own and this gun is no exception. Black powder is corrosive and requires immediate cleaning after field use. Knowing this, the gun has been completely disassembled and cleaned after each use.After shining down the bore with a light, I can say that there is no rust, only lead streaks which can be wiped out with a few patches and Hornady 1-Shot bore cleaner.The gun is accurate with round balls at half charge (50 grains FFFG) and up to 90 grains FFFG (do not exceed) with conicals/sabots. Expect 1.5-3'' groups depending on the day from a bench. If you ruin this rifle with a scope you likely could get the 1'' groups advertised by Hornady.The gun is rather slim which makes for classic lines and good balance but just in case you over tighten the lock screw or drop it on a rock, I am including a replacement lyman factory stock which requires some minor fitting around the lock.The gun is sighted in for 100 yds with the fixed sight shooting conicals and all 3 projectile types impact at the same point a few inches high at 50 yards. I have included the factory buckhorn sight too.I am selling this excellent rifle, replacement lyman factory stock, gun case, 15 Hornady great plains 425-grain conicals, 15 295 grain power belts, the remaining round balls (~70) and cleaning supplies for $800. I would recommend Buffalo arms or Track of the Wolf for black powder. Otherwise, get to know the traditional shooters at Twin Cities Rod and Gun Club. Swiss FFFG seems to work as well as FFFFG for priming the pan.I will respond to emails only. Thank you for looking

Thus you do not need to know the range, you dial the zoom until you have bracketed 18", at which time the lower crosshair shows the estimated holdover, while the upper crosshair shows the normal 200 yd zero (the distance between the wires showing the holdover). Long Live the Second Amendment!Witness Slips Needed!OPPOSE:HB1016 HFA 1 Gun Dealer Licensing Act Amendment 1 has been filed on HB1016 Safety Tech, which would create the Gun Dealer Licensing Act, one of the most onerous assaults on gun rights seen in Illinois in years. It is scheduled for Judiciary - Criminal Committee hearing May 17, 2016 at 1:00PM in Stratton Building Room D-1 Springfield, IL. HB1016, if allowed to become law, will add layer upon layer of red tape to the process of selling firearms, red tape meant not to make society safer but designed to drive gun dealers out of business.HB1016 stipulates that: Dealers must obtain permission from the local sheriff to operate their businessFamily members may not participate in the family business if under age 21Applicants for a license must have 5 years licensee experience and pass a written examEmployees must be licensed in the same way doctors and lawyers are licensed, including continuing education on subjects still to be definedAny person selling more than 8 firearms can be retroactively considered a dealerA license shall not be issued to locations within 500 feet of a school, preschool, or day-care facility, eliminating all possibility of gun stores in Chicago and other cities.Every sale is to be video recorded, available for inspection by State and Federal authorities, which is tantamount to firearm registration!File Your Witness Slip to Oppose To file an electronic witness slip for a committee hearing you will use the section of the Illinois General Assembly website called "My ILGA" (my.ilga.gov). You may speed up the process for filing future witness slips if you set up a free ILGA Dashboard account by going here: Create a New Account. You may file witness slips with or without that free account.If you have an ILGA Dashboard Account, then log on to your ILGA Dashboard, following that return to this email and click this link HB1016 HFA1 - Gun Dealer Licensing Act - to be taken to the witness slip.If you don't have/don't want a My ILGA account you can still just click this link HB1016 HFA1 - Gun Dealer Licensing Act to be taken to the witness slip where you will fill in the information manually for the required fields. REPRESENTATION: Enter "Myself" unless representing an organization. III. POSITION: Indicate your position by selecting the "OPPONENT" radio button for this bill: IV. TESTIMONY: Select the "Record of Appearance Only" radio button., not written testimony. This way, the committee can see a quick count showing the number of people expressing opposition to the bill. title: For Sale:  LWRC IC-SPR 14.7" Piston Upper w/Welded AAC
postcontent: I am selling a great condition LWRC IC-SPR upper reciever that has just been sitting in the safe.  I brought this with a lower, but SBR'd the lower and got a 10.5", thus I have an extra upper.  This upper shoots <1" groups at 100 yards with 75 gr match ammo.  I am looking at getting a longer-barreled REPR or Larue to get some more velocity for longer range shooting.The IC (Individual Carbine) upper includes a unique rail mount that is integrated into the upper reciever, and the 12" rail has a top cover that is removable via thumbscrews to access the piston system.  The mid-length piston system provides a smooth recoil while eliminating gas passage into the bolt carrier or upper reciever.  The spiral fluting on the barrel matches the 1:7 rifle twisting to minimize any heat distortion.  The welded flash hider provides the additional barrel length required by the ATF so a Form 1 is not required.This sale includes the complete upper assembly, including the BCG and folding LWRC skirmish BUIS.Not really looking for any trades.  Price listed OBO.
